        conseils: "If time allows, ask your driver for a stop at Domrémy-la-Pucelle (10 km north of Neufchâteau): Joan of Arc's birthplace (free) is moving in its simplicity, and the Johannic centre (€6) traces the extraordinary epic of the Maid of Orléans. The Bois-Chenu basilica on the hill offers a panorama over the entire Meuse valley. In Nancy, Place Stanislas is a must — this 18th-century square with gilded gates is considered Europe's finest royal square. The École de Nancy Museum (€8) is an Art Nouveau gem. Try quiche lorraine and bergamotes de Nancy at the central market.",
